modules.description: This module offers a string-keyed map implementation with operations for inserting, removing, and querying associations between string keys and arbitrary values, supporting functional transformations like mapping and folding. It enables efficient manipulation of key-value pairs through iteration, filtering, and conversion to/from sequences, tailored for scenarios requiring structured data aggregation or configuration management. The design leverages generic type parameters to accommodate diverse value types while ensuring type safety through string-based key constraints.

Provides functions to parse and generate JSON values from static type definitions, supporting records, variants, and primitive types. Works with OCaml's type system to map between OCaml values and JSON representations. Used to serialize configuration data and deserialize structured logs with guaranteed type safety.

provides a string-keyed map with insert, remove, and query operations, along with functional transformations such as mapping and folding over key-value pairs. It supports iteration, filtering, and conversion to and from sequences, enabling structured data manipulation and configuration handling. The module uses generic types to allow arbitrary value types while enforcing string-based key constraints. Examples include aggregating configuration settings, transforming data structures, and filtering key-value pairs based on custom criteria.
